Node JS:

Node JS is a server side technology.
By using Node JS we can create our own servers.
By using Node JS we can create both http and tcp servers
we can assign the user defined port number to the server.


Modules in Node JS:

1.express
    -- used to develop the rest api.
2.body-parser
    --used to set the MIME Type.
3.mysql module:
    -- used to interact with the mysql database.
4.mongodb
    -- used to interact with the MongoDB.
5.jwt-simple
    -- used to maintain the Token based Authentication system.
